'''''Bucculatrix formosa''''' is a [[moth]] in the [[Bucculatricidae]] family. It is found in the [[Kugitangtau Mountains]] in [[Turkmenistan]].

The length of the forewings is 2.1-2.7&nbsp;mm. The forewings are covered with a mixture of creamish-white and brown or brownish scales. There are two or three dark brown, irregular spots and some irregular, creamish-white areas. The hindwings are creamish-white. Adults have been recorded on wing from August to September.<ref>[http://biostor.org/reference/117055 Bucculatrix formosa sp.n., a remarkable species from the Kugitangtau Mountains (Central Asia) (Lepidoptera: Bucculatricidae)]</ref>

